Prep the ingredients: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ¾-inch wedges. Remove the ribs and stems from the @Kale{4%ounce} and slice or tear the leaves into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and mince the @Shallot{2%ounce}. Using a #flat mallet{} or a #pan{}, crush the @Black Peppercorns{1/2%ounce} inside their bag until coarsely ground.

Roast the potatoes: Toss the potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for ~{30-35%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until the potatoes are tender and golden brown.

Cook the kale: Heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the kale and a splash of @water{a splash} to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until very soft. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Set aside off the heat, but keep the kale in the pan.

Cook the steak: Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Season the @Sirloin Steak{12%ounce} on all sides with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Add the steak to the pan and cook for ~{4-7%minutes} per side, until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Make the peppercorn sauce: Add the shallot and ¼ teaspoon crushed peppercorn (or more, to taste) to the pan, adding a drizzle of oil if necessary. Cook, tossing, ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add the @Beef Stock Concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup} to the pan and scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring to a simmer and reduce until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat, then stir in half the @Sour Cream{2%ounce}.

Cream the kale: Reheat the kale over medium heat, then remove from the heat and stir in the remaining sour cream. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Finish and plate: Slice the steak against the grain, then serve alongside the roasted potatoes and creamed kale. Drizzle the steak with the peppercorn sauce and enjoy!